## Chapter 1: Introduction

## Chapter 2: Document Setup in sketch3

1. Toolbar

   * insert new layers

2. Layers' list

from top to bottom is the z-index of the layers

3. Inspector

## Chapter 3: Design Basics of Sketch3

1. insert Artboard
2. insert rectangle
3. option key + click and drag 
   copy current shape
4. option key and up/down/left/right
   will show the distance to others
5. linear gradient color
6. adding and formatting text
   the center is two part for T: alignment and top bar

## Chapter 4: Beyond the Basics for Sketch3

1. cmd + 2
   take the selection and zoom in the view

2. double click to enter editing mode

3. union as a group and then flatten it 

4. mask 

the bottom layer will be the mask

5. shape fill

## Chapter 5: Symbols and Shared Styles in Sketch3

1. symbol

choose the group and press create a symbol

the name can be separated by slash

replace the group with the symbol

use override to customize the instance of a symbol

2. shared styles

click on the style and create new shared style

Text style

## Chapter 6

1. cmd + G 

to create a group

2. click on the group and cmd + R to rename

3. cmd + arrow -> change the size of a shape


1. Setup

    1. install the Sketch
    2. install Craft for Sketch: https://www.invisionapp.com/craft
    3. https://www.invisionapp.com/

2. Shortcuts
    
    1. Cmd + G: group
    2. Option + Drag: copy an instance
    3. Option + Cmd + C: copy style




